children.subject: Ya, but you're probably wanting an instructor to confirm this

history.content:
I remember reading somewhere in the past that a D in an upper division CS course will still count for the elective, however you still need to maintain a 2.0 overall in the 7 upper division courses to graduate. Can somebody verify this?

For example if I currently have a 3.0 average in 5 upper division CS courses, if I receive a D in the last two courses, I will have an overall upper division GPA of 2.42, will I still be able to graduate or will these two D courses not count toward my 7 completed upper division courses?
history.subject: Upper Division CS Course Grades
